<TITLE> Horlicks Future Forces 2009 winners awarded </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 4 (bdnews24.com)The reality TV show Horlicks Future Forces 2009 that ran for three months with 200 young boys and girls battling it out for top braveryhonours declared the winners on Friday. 'Sameer' and 'Promiti' of Dhaka and 'Anni' of Khulna won the for their outstanding performance in the drills and the psychological tests. In the first phase of the competition, 200 children, aged 8 to 12, from among over 12,000 applicants, were picked. Thirty were selected in the primary test and only five for the final round. Nurul Islam Nahid, the education minister, and deputy editor of Daily Prothom Alo Anisul Huq awarded the winners in a colourful ceremony at Hotel Sheraton. Nahid said, "The competition is very significant as a huge number of kids participated and showed their bravery." Children can also learn from the activities outside the books and schools that can make their life easier. This sort of competitions should be expanded, he added. Managing director of GlaxoSmithKline Bangladesh Azizul Huq and country manager Raghuvir U Krishnan awarded the three scholarships worth Tk 5 lakh and desktop computers. The winners from the fourth to ninth would be awarded desktop computers.
